[+++ b/docs/reference/search/aggregations.asciidoc, +[float], +=== Returning only aggregation results, +, +There are many occasions when aggregations are required but search hits are not.  For these cases the hits can be ignored by , +adding `search_type=count` to the request URL parameters. For example:, +, +[source,js], +--------------------------------------------------, +$ curl -XGET 'http://localhost:9200/twitter/tweet/_search?search_type=count' -d '{, +  "aggregations": {, +    "my_agg": {, +      "terms": {, +        "field": "text", +      }, +    }, +  }, +}, +', +--------------------------------------------------, +, +Setting `search_type` to `count` avoids executing the fetch phase of the search making the request more efficient.  See , +<<search-request-search-type>> for more information on the `search_type` parameter.]